SYNOPSIS
        object clone_limited_object(string name, int limit)
DESCRIPTION
        Clones a new object much like the clone_object efun would.
        The difference, however, is that clone_limited_object will
        register the new object with the unique tracking system
        and only allow a limited number of instances of the object to
        be in the game at a given time.
        
        Note that the pathname must be complete, which means there 
        are no relative paths allowed.

        NOTE: clone_limited_object will not check if the object in
              question has been cloned before using clone_object.
              Thus, it is entirely possible to clone several instances
              of an object using clone_object and still get a valid
              object from clone_limited_object even after there are more
              objects in the game than desired. However, all calls to
              clone_limited_object itself fully respect object limitations.
              
EXAMPLE
        // Clone limited sword
        object sword, sword2, sword3;

        sword = clone_limited_object("/obj/sword", 2);
        sword2 = clone_limited_object("/obj/sword", 2);
        sword3 = clone_limited_object("/obj/sword", 2);

        // Sword 3 above will be 0, since only two swords
        // will be allowed in-game at a time.

